### Summary Table for Interviews

| Subcommand | K8s Type | Best Used For |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **generic** | `Opaque` | General app secrets (Passwords, API keys). |
| **tls** | `kubernetes.io/tls` | HTTPS certificates (`tls.crt`, `tls.key`). |
| **docker-registry**| `kubernetes.io/dockerconfigjson` | Pulling private images. |
| (N/A) | `kubernetes.io/ssh-auth` | SSH Private keys. |

**Pro-Tip:** If you're asked in an interview why we use different types if they all just store Base64 data, the answer is **validation**. Kubernetes can perform basic "sanity checks" on specific types (like ensuring a TLS secret has both a certificate and a key) to help prevent configuration errors.